<dl id="n22035k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n22" href="#n22035k">N22 (VI.B.17)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n22all.htm#n22035k"> 35(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Demosthenes lives underground / half head shaved <small>Blue</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n22035k"><li>FW 494.24 </li><li><a href="../../flex/rA/lexrA.htm#n22035k">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/rA/l39rA.htm#n22035k">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n22035k">MS BL 47484a-261v</ms> </li><li>JJA 58:340 <a name="rAd8" href="../../FF/fdra/rda.htm#rAd8">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/rA/rAd8.htm#n22035k">Draft: III&sect;3A.8</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;D&egrave;s ce moment, il fit construire un cabinet souterrain qui subsistait encore de mon temps (1), dans lequel il allait tous les jours s&apos;exercer &agrave; la d&eacute;clamation et former sa voix. Il y passait jusqu&apos;&agrave; deux ou trois mois de suite, ayant la moiti&eacute; de la t&ecirc;te ras&eacute;e, afin que la honte de para&icirc;tre en cet &eacute;tat l&apos;emp&ecirc;ch&acirc;t de sortir, quelque envie qu&apos;il en e&ucirc;t.&rdquo; <small> Arthur Chervin, <a name="STUTT" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#STUTT"><cite title="source">B&eacute;gaiement et autres maladies fonctionnelles de la parole</cite></a> (1902) 407</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Demosthenes shut himself up in an underground study, having first guarded himself against a longing for the haunts of men by shaving one side of his head.</mm> </dd></dl>
